Jack Swigert is raised to the recovery helicopter after splashdown.
Thumbs up from Gerry Griffin
Fred Haise (left), Jim Lovell, and Jack Swigert emerge from the recovery helicopter on-board the aircraft carrier Iwo Jima.
Mission Control in Houston celebrates the safe return of the Apollo 13 crew. Gene Kranz is smoking a celebratory cigar at the right while Deke Slayton, in front of the mission patch, shakes hands.
Recovery prayer
Rear Admiral Donald C. Davis (USN), Recovery Task Force Commander, welcomes Fred Haise (left), Jack Swigert, and Jim Lovell aboard the U.S. Iwo Jima after their safe return to Earth.
Navy divers pose with the Command Module before it is hoisted aboard the Iwo Jima.

The Apollo 13 Command Module being hosted aboard the Iwo Jima. 17 April 1970.
The Apollo 13 Command Module after being hosted aboard the Iwo Jima.
Jim Lovell (left), Fred Haise, and Jack Swigert receive a phone call on board the Iwo Jima. The fact that it is a group call and that a photo was taken suggest that the call is from President Nixon.
Jim Lovell reads a newspaper account of the Apollo 13 recovery.
U. S. President Richard Nixon (right) welcomes the Apollo 13 crew safely home. Jack Swigert is at the left, then Fred Haise, and Jim Lovell. 18 April 1970.
Fred Haise (left), Jim Lovell, President Nixon, and Jack Swigert at Hickham Air Force Base, Hawaii. 18 April 1970.
